Was reading a good /x/ thread about the sinking of the MV Sewol ferry in South Korea where hundreds of schoolchildren died being an intentional human sacrifice related to the "8 goddesses" cult the Korean president was involved with. The thread is still up if you want to read it.

In many ways the sinking is similar to the Russian Kursk submarine disaster I posted about the other day. Generally I think when you have a case of multiple level extreme gross negligence involving diff orgs it's very sensible to suspect something is deeply wrong with the story.

Even in provincial backwater hick hospitals e.g. if you go to the ICU the doctors are extremely competent and actually know what they're doing. To have simultaneous failure of captain/crew, regulatory agency, Coast Guard, first response teams, etc. seems almost fantastical to me.

Generally the more you read about South Korean society the more it seems like it's on the same level of batshit insanity as North Korea, like it's not the totalitarian communism doing it there, that's just how Koreans are by default. Mountain shamanism, death cults, secrecy, etc.

Apparently Dr. Michael Aquino of psy-op fame was really into stimulants, from amphetamines to ginseng tea. Lesson in here. If he knew about thyroid therapy we could have probably avoided the entire satanism pedophilia fiasco. Always listen to what your body is trying to tell you.
